Sentencas: The crystal structure and oxygen stoichiometry of the proposed double perovskite solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anode material PrBaMn2O5+delta were determined under SOFC anode conditions via in-situ neutron diffraction.
Titulo: Structural analysis of PrBaMn2O5+δ under SOFC anode conditions by in-situ neutron powder diffraction

Sentencas: Measurements were performed in reducing atmospheres between 692 K and 984 K. The structure was fit to a tetragonal (space group P4/mmm) layered double perovskite structure with alternating Pr and Ba A-site cation layers.
Titulo: Structural analysis of PrBaMn2O5+δ under SOFC anode conditions by in-situ neutron powder diffraction

Sentencas: Under all conditions examined, the oxygen sites in the Ba and Mn layers were fully occupied, while the sites in the Pr layer were close to completely vacant.
Titulo: Structural analysis of PrBaMn2O5+δ under SOFC anode conditions by in-situ neutron powder diffraction

Sentencas: The results of the neutron diffraction experiments are compared to previous thermogravimetric analysis experiments to verify the accuracy of both experiments.
Titulo: Structural analysis of PrBaMn2O5+δ under SOFC anode conditions by in-situ neutron powder diffraction

Sentencas: PrBaMn2O5+delta was shown to be stable over a wide range of reducing atmospheres similar to anode operating conditions in solid oxide fuel cells without significant structural changes.
Titulo: Structural analysis of PrBaMn2O5+δ under SOFC anode conditions by in-situ neutron powder diffraction
